HEADWORD: Hutchunsonian
<hw>Hutch`un*so"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A follower
of John <xex>Hutchinson</xex> of Yorkshire, England, who believed that
the Hebrew Scriptures contained a complete system of natural science and
of theology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huttonian</ent>⟦br⟧
